title: Poland Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Poland Three Month Interbank Rate was at 7.49 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Poland averaged 7.84 percent from 1994 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 29.58 percent in March of 1995 and a record low of 0.11 percent in December of 2020. In Poland, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Poland Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of Poland
